                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/16</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-12T11:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 11, midnight. Am in Juarez conferring with General Gavira
                    and Consul Garcia. They are endeavoring to comply with Department’s request
                    transmitted by me. General Gavira states he has already sent troops out on
                    Northwestern road from Juarez and that he has been informed by General Treviño
                    that troops have already been sent west from Chihuahua over that division of
                    Northwestern.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
